SIMPLE: gremial
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gremial
<hw>Gre"mi*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>gremium</ets> lap, bosom.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the lap
or bosom.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gremial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gremial
<hw>Gre"mi*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A bosom friend.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Ecol.)</fld> <def>A cloth, often adorned with gold
or silver lace, placed on the bishop's lap while he sits in celebrating
mass, or in ordaining priests.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grenade</ent>⟦br⟧
